OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FC4 subtitle problems       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbreached licence           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fconditions, Ofcom finds    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Channel 4 breached its broadcast       
OL,6, licence conditions after viewers had to
OL,7, go weeks without subtitles, signing or 
OL,8, audio description, Ofcom has found.    
OL,10,FThe media watchdog said the channel    
OL,11,Fmissed its subtitles quota on Freesat  
OL,12,Ffor 2021, after a fire at a broadcast  
OL,13,Fcentre affected services last autumn.  
OL,15,FChannel 4 said it was "very            
OL,16,Fdisappointed with Ofcom's decision and 
OL,17,Fwill review its findings carefully.    
OL,19,F"We would like to apologise once again 
OL,20,Fto our audiences for the disruption."  
